{"id":1236,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":1236,"title":"Vine","subtitle":"","short_title":"Vine","uri":"/scriptures/bd/vine","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/vine.t1","order":".000.3958"},[".title","Vine"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/vine.p1","order":".000.3959"},"Palestine has always been famous for its vines (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/deut/8.7-8"},"Deut. 8:7–8"],"). The growing of grapes was part of the regular occupation of the Israelites after the settlement in Canaan. The vine was frequently regarded as a symbol of the Jewish or Christian Church (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ps/80.8-17"},"Ps. 80:8–17"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/isa/5.1-7"},"Isa. 5:1–7"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/isa/27.2-3"},"27:2–3"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/jer/2.21"},"Jer. 2:21"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ezek/19.10-14"},"Ezek. 19:10–14"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/21.33-40"},"Matt. 21:33–40"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/12.1-9"},"Mark 12:1–9"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/20.9-16"},"Luke 20:9–16"],"; see especially",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/15.1-8"},"John 15:1–8"],")."]]],"refs":null}
